article.description: Four McGlynn had 16 points, Earl Watson added 14 points and Rhode Island beat Saint Louis 85-57 in the Atlantic 10 opener for both teams on Saturday.
article.headline: Rhode Island cruises in A10 opener, 85-57 over Saint Louis
article.linkText: Rhode Island cruises in A10 opener, 85-57 over Saint Louis
article.story: KINGSTON, R.I. -- Four McGlynn had 16 points, Earl Watson added 14 points and Rhode Island beat Saint Louis 85-57 in the Atlantic 10 opener for both teams on Saturday. McGlynn sank four 3-pointers and Watson took and made all six of his field-goal attempts in the second half. Rhode Island (9-5) had balanced scoring with Jarvis Garrett and Jared Terrell adding 13 apiece and Kuran Iverson scoring 12 points with eight rebounds. The Rams opened the game with an 18-2 run and had a 42-24 lead at the half. They stayed in front by at least 14 after the break to win their second in a row while handing Saint Louis (5-8) its fifth straight loss. Miles Reynolds and Ash Yacoubou scored 12 points each to lead the Billikens, who made just 3 of 15 from 3-point range.
